<P><PB N="51" REF="55">
I &s;hould oppo&s;e any diminution
whatever of the number of the Lords
of Se&s;&s;ion, becau&s;e it would make "the
law's delay" be more grievou&s;ly felt:
but, above all, I di&s;like this particular
plot, to revive the <HI>Decemviri.</HI> It is
<HI>ominous.</HI> In the words of <HI>Livy</HI> I will
&s;ay, <Q><HI>Non placere nomen; periculo&s;um
libertati e&s;&s;e.</HI></Q></P>
<P><HI>Who</HI> &s;econded the King's Advo|cate's
motion for leave to bring in
this bill&mdash;this odious bill of pains
and penalties?&mdash;It was Sir <HI>Adam Fer|gu&s;&s;on;</HI>
a man who has vexed me
not a little, by his political &s;ucce&s;s in
our county, again&s;t my wi&s;hes. He is
one whom Mr. Dundas has &s;elected to
