is &s;aid</HI> he &s;upports the earl's friend
for one parliament, and the earl is to
make him member next parliament<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">When the report of this curious agreement bur&s;t upon the county, like a bomb, and &s;tunned men of all parties, I made the following Bell|man's rhimes, to u&s;her in my friend Colonel Hugh Montgomerie as our repre&s;entative:
<LG>
<L>Adam, too long you've kept your &s;eat,</L>
